The paper deals with online algorithms for combinatorial packing problems, which are typically studied in the computer science subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of competitive analysis suggests that game theory (cs.GT) may also be relevant. The study of expected number of postponements involves probability and information theory (cs.IT), while the use of approximation algorithms suggests machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI) as possible subfields.
